meanings.definition: To surpass in sinning or committing evil deeds.
meanings.sent1: She always tries to outsin her rival in their wicked schemes.
meanings.sent2: He believes he can outsin anyone in the neighborhood.
meanings.sent3: The two villains had a competition to see who could outsin the other first.
meanings.sent4: Her dark intentions seemed to outsin even the most notorious criminals.
meanings.sent5: The evil queen's desire to outsin all her enemies knew no bounds.

meanings.definition: To be more sinful or wicked than someone else.
meanings.sent1: He tends to outsin his friends when it comes to mischievous pranks.
meanings.sent2: The notorious pirate captain was known to outsin all his crewmates.
meanings.sent3: The mischievous cat tried to outsin the dog in causing trouble around the house.
meanings.sent4: Her devious plan to outsin her rival was carefully crafted and executed.
meanings.sent5: The dark wizard's power to outsin others was unmatched in the realm.
